displayName: City of the Grasslands, Campus - Tavern/Inn 1F

parameters: Priestess Sophia: So, do you have any business with me?
Clea: Um, actually, I have a request--
Bar Owner: Hey, the payment... you're leaving it behind.
Mage Relm: Let's chase after them quickly!
Mage Relm: Who are you? We're in a hurry, you know!
Bard: Well... I guess it's fine for now.

Bard: You all seem like adventurers. I would like to consult
with you when you have some free time.
Clea: Understood, I will call out to her.
Clea: First, let's chase after Sophia-san.
Bard: Now, I wonder what kind of story they will tell us?

It was the first impression of the brave ones who saw Clea
and the others. They had a premonition of an enchanting
story.

I was convinced that Relm could become a threat to the
world, but at the moment there was no immediate need to do
something. Therefore, my main interest was in their story.

If you were to compare a person to a book, it would be like
reading a partway through the book. Just from that, you can
imagine that there is a wonderful story before and after.

Like when I met the man who once became the king of the
empire, like when I met the man who was once the first guild
master of the adventurer's guild, like when I met the man
who once became an archmage.

A gust of wind blew through the hearts that were like a
desert, where everything had come to a standstill. For the
brave ones, meeting those who hold stories was exactly like
this.

And just like that, there were four of them. I can't help
but expect that something big might happen. I find myself
wishing to etch it into my own heart without fail.

Perhaps the heroes haven't lost as much as they think. There
may be some trigger that allows them to remember a little
bit.

That might be the reason why I became a bard. And the
battles with the girls are etched into the heart of this
tone-deaf bard.

That will someday become a poem and be engraved in the
hearts of children. It may be subtle for the heroes, but it
was enjoyable.
